otherwise relate wholly or mainly to the maintenance or upbringing of a minor

Subsection 1(a) as originally enacted stated “where the proceedings relate to the wardship or adoption of an infant or wholly or mainly to the guardianship, custody, maintenance or upbringing of an infant, or rights of access to an infant”. The current form of wording was substituted by the Children Act 1989 Sch.13 para.14 with effect from 14 October 1991. The change of language makes no difference to the reportability issue.
